This is code for Slackbot to automatically send files.

Steps to setup:
Configure Permissions: In the "OAuth & Permissions" section, add scopes like files:write and chat:write to allow sending messages and files.
Get a Bot Token: Get the bot token from your app.

Code Explanation:
uploadFileToSlack: This function reads a file and uploads it to Slack using the File Upload API.
Multipart Form: Uses a multipart form to upload the file and additional fields, such as the channel.
Authorization: The Authorization header includes the Slack bot token, which must have the necessary permissions.
Remember to replace slackBotToken and channelID with the appropriate values. This code will be able to upload a specified file to a channel or user in Slack.